2
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:48,300
高鳴る心臓に祈りを乗せて
With my prayers loaded into my beating heart,

3
00:02:48,300 --> 00:02:51,300
曖昧な夢を描く
I draw a vague dream.

4
00:02:51,300 --> 00:02:54,200
幻想は想像のまま
The fantasy remains as just imagination,

5
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:57,100
終われないんだ
it cannot end like this.

6
00:03:01,300 --> 00:03:04,200
みんなー！今日見に来てくれてありがとう！
Everyone! Thank you so much for coming to watch today!

7
00:03:06,300 --> 00:03:09,900
答えを永遠と探し続けて
Continuously searching for the answer for eternity,

8
00:03:09,900 --> 00:03:13,100
何者かになりたくて
longing to become someone.

9
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:17,300
燦々と降る夕立をただ眺めた
I merely stared at the brilliantly falling evening shower.

10
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:22,300
優しく寄り添って 心が晴れるのなら
If gently nestling close clears up my heart,

11
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:27,200
翼が生えたような気がして
I feel as if wings have sprouted,

12
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:32,000
いつだって隣にいるから
because I will always be right by your side.

13
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:36,500
だって言葉紡いで歌うことが
Because spinning words and singing...

14
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:39,100
...あたしの運命だ
...is my destiny.

15
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:41,800
世界にありふれた虚しささえも
Even the emptiness that floods the world,

16
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:44,200
上書きして
I will overwrite it.

17
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:47,800
路地裏に咲いた花のように
Like a flower blooming in a back alley,

18
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:50,000
願いを照らす
I will illuminate wishes...

19
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:55,200
小さな光に憧れて
...longing for that small light.

20
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:09,500
名前も持たない歌なんて
A song that doesn't even have a name...

21
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:12,400
神様なら認めてくれない
...God would surely never recognize it.

22
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:17,300
ひとつひとつ枯れない花のように
But like a flower that never withers,

23
00:04:17,300 --> 00:04:20,500
昨日の自分にさよならして
I say goodbye to the me of yesterday.

24
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:23,200
こぼれた涙
With my spilled tears,

25
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:29,000
うまく笑えなくてもいいかな
is it okay even if I can't smile well?

26
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:32,800
だって理想は遠ざかってくばかり
Because my ideals keep drifting further away,

27
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,900
もう散々だ
it's already a complete disaster.

28
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:37,800
どれだけ手を伸ばして叫んだって
No matter how much I reach out and scream,

29
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:40,100
届かないの
it doesn't reach.

30
00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:43,000
望めばいつか叶うはずって
Because I believe that if I wish for it,

31
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,700
信じてるから
it will come true someday.

32
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:52,000
どうか歌よ響いて
Please, let my song resonate!

33
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:57,200
あぁ、心臓の鼓動が今日も
Ah, the beating of my heart...

34
00:04:57,200 --> 00:04:59,900
うるさい
...is so loud again today.

35
00:05:00,888 --> 00:05:05,788
行き止まりばっか足が竦んで 立てないよ
My feet freeze at every dead end, I can't even stand

36
00:05:05,788 --> 00:05:11,988
音のない世界から君を見つけて 連れ出すんだ
I'll find you in this soundless world and take you away

37
00:05:11,988 --> 00:05:16,988
言葉紡いで唄うことが わたしの運命だ
Weaving words and singing is my destiny

38
00:05:16,988 --> 00:05:22,688
世界にありふれた虚しささえも 上書きして
Overwriting even the emptiness so common in this world

39
00:05:22,688 --> 00:05:28,588
路地裏に咲いた花のように 願いを照らす
Like a flower blooming in a back alley, illuminating wishes

40
00:05:28,588 --> 00:05:32,988
小さな光に憧れて
Yearning for that tiny light

41
00:05:37,388 --> 00:05:45,788
君の歌姫になれたら いいな
I hope I can become your diva

42
00:06:06,888 --> 00:06:10,888
Dancing Reed / 作詞・作曲・編曲：アオワイファイ
[Song: Dancing Reed / Lyrics, Composition, Arrangement: Aowai-fai]

43
00:06:12,988 --> 00:06:19,388
okey dokey返事はいいけど 冗談なら笑えないよ
Okey-dokey, your reply is fine, but if it's a joke, it's not funny

44
00:06:19,388 --> 00:06:26,388
渋態曖昧どっちを向いちゃうの 蜃気楼に手を伸ばした
Congested and vague, which way are you turning? I reached my hand out to the mirage

45
00:06:26,388 --> 00:06:30,888
微熱のような夢物語
A daydream like a slight fever

46
00:06:30,888 --> 00:06:34,888
そんな光は見ない振りしていた
I pretended not to see that kind of light

47
00:06:34,888 --> 00:06:38,688
ざわめく鼓動まだ行かないで
My fluttering heartbeat, please don't fade away yet

48
00:06:38,688 --> 00:06:42,388
幻じゃ嫌だよ 私を奪って
I don't want it to be an illusion, sweep me away

49
00:06:42,388 --> 00:06:45,388
魅惑のdancing dancing night
A captivating dancing, dancing night

50
00:06:45,388 --> 00:06:48,388
拡がって収まんないuniverse
An expanding, uncontrollable universe

51
00:06:48,388 --> 00:06:52,888
君の表情は私の森羅万象を
Your expression completely rewrites

52
00:06:52,888 --> 00:06:56,588
書き換えちゃうかも責任重大ね
my whole universe, you hold a heavy responsibility

53
00:06:56,588 --> 00:06:59,088
一切合切
Everything, absolutely everything

54
00:06:59,088 --> 00:07:02,188
dance dance dance we are dancing reed

55
00:07:02,188 --> 00:07:04,388
夢中になって絡み合ったゼログラビティ
Falling head over heels in this entangled zero gravity

56
00:07:04,388 --> 00:07:07,588
構わず dance dance dance
Without a care, dance, dance, dance

57
00:07:07,588 --> 00:07:10,788
just a dance just a dance

58
00:07:10,788 --> 00:07:14,088
声は闇に預けたまま
With our voices left to the darkness

59
00:07:14,088 --> 00:07:18,188
目を覚ましても離れないで
Even when I wake up, please don't leave me

60
00:07:21,888 --> 00:07:25,388
maybe needy正気じゃないのよ
Maybe needy, I'm not in my right mind

61
00:07:25,388 --> 00:07:28,888
体温が忘れられない
I can't forget your warmth

62
00:07:28,888 --> 00:07:31,888
誰彼そんなじゃないから
I'm not like this with just anyone

63
00:07:31,888 --> 00:07:35,788
独り占めしてeuphoria
Keeping this euphoria all to myself

64
00:07:35,788 --> 00:07:39,088
気にしてない様な言葉は装飾で
My words pretending not to care are just decorations

65
00:07:39,088 --> 00:07:42,988
メイクの様には流せない
They can't be washed away like makeup

66
00:07:42,988 --> 00:07:46,888
360°偽りだって
Even if it's 360 degrees of lies

67
00:07:46,888 --> 00:07:49,888
隠しきれぬような
And I can't completely hide them

68
00:07:49,888 --> 00:07:53,888
私に構って嬉しいなんて crazy crazy love
Being happy that you notice me is a crazy, crazy love

69
00:07:53,888 --> 00:07:57,388
摩天楼から連れさらって
Sweep me away from this skyscraper

70
00:07:57,388 --> 00:08:01,888
君の表情は私の深層心理を
Your expression completely alters

71
00:08:01,888 --> 00:08:05,088
すり替えちゃうのよ責任重大ね
my deepest feelings, you hold a heavy responsibility

72
00:08:05,088 --> 00:08:09,388
過ぎ去ったネオン 残像shooting star
Passing neons, the afterimage of a shooting star

73
00:08:21,388 --> 00:08:24,888
グライダーみたいに漂えば
If I drifted like a glider

74
00:08:24,888 --> 00:08:28,088
幸も不幸もなかった
there would be neither happiness nor unhappiness

75
00:08:28,088 --> 00:08:31,888
指先でまた君を探している
With my fingertips, I'm searching for you again

76
00:08:31,888 --> 00:08:35,088
その声を聴かせてよ
Let me hear your voice

77
00:08:35,088 --> 00:08:39,088
私に構って 教えてよ恋の先を！
Notice me, and tell me what lies beyond love!

78
00:08:39,088 --> 00:08:42,388
拡がって収まんないuniverse
An expanding, uncontrollable universe

79
00:08:42,388 --> 00:08:46,888
君の存在は私の将来までも
Your existence has stepped

80
00:08:46,888 --> 00:08:49,888
踏み込んだのよ付き合ってよね
into my future, so stay with me, okay?

81
00:08:49,888 --> 00:08:52,388
一切合切
Everything, absolutely everything

82
00:08:52,388 --> 00:08:55,688
dance dance dance we are dancing reed

83
00:08:55,688 --> 00:08:57,888
夢中になって絡み合ったゼログラビティ
Falling head over heels in this entangled zero gravity

84
00:08:57,888 --> 00:09:01,088
構わず dance dance dance
Without a care, dance, dance, dance

85
00:09:01,088 --> 00:09:04,388
just a dance just a dance

86
00:09:04,388 --> 00:09:07,688
声は闇に預けたまま
With our voices left to the darkness

87
00:09:07,688 --> 00:09:11,988
目を覚ましても離れないで
Even when I wake up, please don't leave me

88
00:09:24,888 --> 00:09:30,888
みんなー！今日は誕生日ライブに来てくれてありがとう！
Everyone! Thank you so much for coming to my birthday live stream today!

89
00:09:30,888 --> 00:09:35,388
きゃー！コメントも見えてるよー！
Kyaa! I can see your comments too!

90
00:09:35,388 --> 00:09:39,888
最初に聴いてもらったのが「Diva」「Dancing Reed」でした！
The first two songs you heard were 'Diva' and 'Dancing Reed'!

91
00:09:39,888 --> 00:09:45,888
えー、この二つの曲は、あのフェスと、あと去年のね、ドラマの主題歌に使わせて...
Um, these two songs were used for that festival, and also as the theme songs for last year's drama...

92
00:09:45,888 --> 00:09:50,888
使っていただいた曲で、すごく思い出に残っているので...
...and they hold really special memories for me,

93
00:09:50,888 --> 00:09:54,688
最初に二曲歌ってみようかなと思って選びました！
so I chose them to perform as the first two songs!

94
00:09:54,688 --> 00:10:00,688
そして、今回はですね、ときのそらお披露目誕生日...
And this time, it's 'Tokino Sora 3D Showcase & Birthday...'

95
00:10:00,688 --> 00:10:04,888
2026！「ときのそらお」じゃないよ、ときのそらだよ！って
2026! It's not 'Tokino Sorao,' it's Tokino Sora! Haha,

96
00:10:04,129 --> 00:10:08,329
ええ、みんなの呟きを待ってるので、たくさん呟いてほしいな。
Yeah, I'm waiting for everyone's tweets, so please tweet a lot.

97
00:10:08,529 --> 00:10:10,629
トレンドに入るかな？
Will we get into the trending topics?

98
00:10:11,229 --> 00:10:13,129
ねー？
Right?

99
00:10:13,629 --> 00:10:17,729
そして、今回のテーマは、8周年を象徴する、無限をモチーフに
And, this time's theme is based on infinity, which symbolizes our 8th anniversary.

100
00:10:17,829 --> 00:10:22,129
宇宙や星をステージに散りばめて、中毒性のあるビート、
We've scattered space and stars across the stage with an addictive beat...

101
00:10:22,129 --> 00:10:27,129
リズムの曲で絡めた、えー、デジタルパルスライブです！
combined with rhythmic songs... yes, it's a Digital Pulse Live!

102
00:10:27,629 --> 00:10:30,429
デジタルパルスライブです！
It's a Digital Pulse Live!

103
00:10:30,629 --> 00:10:35,129
こちらね、大きな天球が曲によってどう変わるのかを見ていてください。
Please look at how this large celestial sphere changes depending on the song.

104
00:10:35,329 --> 00:10:38,629
そしてね、今年ののんのんは、えー、いつつなので、
And also, this year's Non-Non... there are five of them,

105
00:10:38,629 --> 00:10:41,929
くるくる回転してます。くるくるくるくるくるくる...
so they are spinning round and round. Round and round and round...

106
00:10:42,129 --> 00:10:45,329
そして、夜空にはソラザウルスもいるよ。
And, there's also a Sorasaurus in the night sky.

107
00:10:45,329 --> 00:10:50,629
ソラザウルスはね、なんとね、炎を出せるようになりました。
The Sorasaurus can now breathe fire!

108
00:10:50,929 --> 00:10:52,629
ぽぅっ！
Whoosh!

109
00:10:53,129 --> 00:10:58,129
ちゃんと、アンキモ座もあるんですけど、見えるかな？
There's also the Ankimo Constellation, can you see it?

110
00:11:00,129 --> 00:11:04,129
もちろん、あと今年も新衣装のお披露目や、告知したゲストと、
Of course, there's also the reveal of new outfits, and our announced guests...

111
00:11:04,129 --> 00:11:08,329
あとは、どんな曲を披露するのかを楽しみにしててくだいさいね！
and look forward to what kind of songs we'll perform!

112
00:11:08,629 --> 00:11:13,629
そして、次に行く前に、ぷちお披露目、最初にしちゃいましょう！
And before we move on, let's start with a mini-reveal first!

113
00:11:13,729 --> 00:11:16,429
カメラさん、上を向いてください。
Camera-san, please look up.

114
00:11:19,129 --> 00:11:21,129
はい！
Yes!

115
00:11:21,129 --> 00:11:28,129
はい、というわけで、新しいクラゲヘア、新髪型お披露目です！
Yes! So, here is the reveal of my new jellyfish hairstyle!

116
00:11:28,129 --> 00:11:34,129
それでは早速、ゲストパートに行ってみよう！可愛い、ありがとう！おお、可愛い、ありがとう！
Now then, let's head straight into the guest segment! 'Cute,' thank you! Oh, 'cute,' thank you!

117
00:11:34,329 --> 00:11:37,329
シロ組さんもいっぱいコメントしててね！
Siro-gumi members, please leave lots of comments too!

118
00:11:37,329 --> 00:11:41,129
最初のゲストは、この人です！
The first guest is this person!

119
00:12:08,129 --> 00:12:10,129
GUEST: 電脳少女シロ
[Guest: Cyber Girl Siro]

120
00:12:23,629 --> 00:12:25,929
星を降らすたびに...
Every time I make the stars fall...

121
00:12:25,929 --> 00:12:27,929
心寄せるたびに...
Every time we draw our hearts closer...

122
00:12:27,929 --> 00:12:31,629
迷い込んだ夜はギャラクティカ！
The night we wandered in is Galactica!

123
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:40,129
明星ギャラクティカ
作詞・作曲：ナユタン星人
[Song: Meisei Galactica
Lyrics/Composition: Nayutan Seijin]

124
00:12:42,329 --> 00:12:45,629
今夜はソラノアイをライトが...
Tonight, the light on Sora's eyes (Sora no Ai)...

125
00:12:45,629 --> 00:12:48,329
嫌に眩しいから...
is awfully blinding.

126
00:12:48,529 --> 00:12:50,129
街のネオンを...
So the neon lights of the town...

127
00:12:50,129 --> 00:12:51,929
さあ取りよせ...
now, gather them here.

128
00:12:51,929 --> 00:12:55,629
明星ギャラクティカ、2人で。
Meisei Galactica, the two of us.

129
00:12:55,629 --> 00:12:58,129
シドけないくらい...
So seductive...

130
00:12:58,129 --> 00:13:02,129
ユラユラ 揺らぐ星が 心まどわすから...
The swaying, trembling stars bewitch my heart.

131
00:13:02,129 --> 00:13:03,629
この夜だけ... whale
Only for this night...

132
00:13:03,629 --> 00:13:04,929
君だけ...
only you...

133
00:13:04,929 --> 00:13:08,929
夜空に 星を 星を 駆ける...
race through the stars in the night sky.

134
00:13:10,629 --> 00:13:12,629
見つめて あなたの表情...
Look at me, your expression...

135
00:13:12,629 --> 00:13:15,329
照らして 明星ギャラクティカ...
illuminates the Meisei Galactica.

136
00:13:15,329 --> 00:13:16,729
見上げた...
Looking up...

137
00:13:16,729 --> 00:13:17,929
夜空は...
at the night sky...

138
00:13:17,929 --> 00:13:19,629
一等星が...
the first-magnitude star...

139
00:13:19,629 --> 00:13:23,129
チラリ チラって光る...
flickers and shines.

140
00:13:23,629 --> 00:13:25,629
チカチカ 踊り踊って...
Twinkle, twinkle, dancing along...

141
00:13:25,629 --> 00:13:27,329
孤独を溶かして...
melting away loneliness.

142
00:13:27,329 --> 00:13:30,629
2人の影で...
With our two shadows,

143
00:15:01,117 --> 00:15:03,617
わー！
Wow!

144
00:15:27,117 --> 00:15:30,617
はい！というわけで最初のゲストは、
Yes! And so, our very first guest is...

145
00:15:30,617 --> 00:15:33,117
シロちゃんだよー！
Siro-chan!

146
00:15:33,117 --> 00:15:35,617
こんにちは！ときの、シロです！
Hello! I'm Tokino Siro!

147
00:15:36,117 --> 00:15:38,117
ときのシロになっちゃった！
You became 'Tokino Siro'!

148
00:15:39,117 --> 00:15:44,617
本当に今日は、そらちゃん、お誕生日おめでとうございます！
Sora-chan, happy birthday! Thank you so much for today!

149
00:15:44,617 --> 00:15:46,617
ありがとう！
Thank you!

150
00:15:46,617 --> 00:15:48,617
すごいね、格好！
Your outfit is amazing!

151
00:15:49,117 --> 00:15:53,617
そらちゃんという歌姫にお会いできると聞いて、出せるものは全部出して行こうと思います。
When I heard I could meet a diva like Sora-chan, I thought I should show everything I've got.

152
00:15:54,617 --> 00:15:56,617
そ、そういうことだったんだ。
Oh, so that's what it was.

153
00:15:57,117 --> 00:16:00,617
待って、これチャンネルBANしちゃう...
Wait, isn't this going to get our channel banned?

154
00:16:00,617 --> 00:16:02,617
そんなことない！ごめんなさい！
No way! I'm sorry!

155
00:16:02,617 --> 00:16:06,617
大丈夫、大丈夫だから。胸が苦しくなってきました、大丈夫。
It's fine, it's fine! My chest is getting a bit tight now, but I'm fine!

156
00:16:07,617 --> 00:16:10,617
そらちゃん、クラゲさんには、注射器があると聞きます。
Sora-chan, I hear jellyfish have syringes.

157
00:16:10,617 --> 00:16:12,617
注射器？
Syringes?

158
00:16:12,617 --> 00:16:16,117
毒針をぜひ、頭でごちゅんと、シロに刺していただけませんか？
Would you please sting Siro on the head with your poison needle, like 'boop'?

159
00:16:16,617 --> 00:16:18,617
ごちゅん！
*Boop!*

160
00:16:18,617 --> 00:16:21,117
うっ、うう...
Ugh, oooh...

161
00:16:21,117 --> 00:16:23,617
倒れる、倒れちゃうから！
You're collapsing! You're going to fall!

162
00:16:22,117 --> 00:16:24,617
すごい効いてきました！
It's really working!

163
00:16:24,617 --> 00:16:25,617
効いてきた？
It's working?!

164
00:16:25,617 --> 00:16:30,617
皆さん、そらちゃんは変わりました。毒針を持った女に変わったんです！
Everyone, Sora-chan has changed! She has changed into a woman with a poison needle!

165
00:16:30,617 --> 00:16:32,617
私強くなったから！
I've gotten stronger, after all!

166
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:36,617
そらちゃんは毒針が持ちたくて、可愛いクラゲヘアになったんですか？
Did you get this cute jellyfish hair because you wanted a poison needle, Sora-chan?

167
00:16:37,117 --> 00:16:45,617
違うよ違うよ。私、やっぱアイドルと言えば、こういう可愛い髪型の人が多いかなと思って、そういうアイドルっぽい髪型にしたいなと思ってたんだよね。
No, no! I just thought cute hairstyles like this are common for idols, so I wanted to try an idol-like hairstyle.

168
00:16:46,617 --> 00:16:57,617
そらちゃん、聞いてください。シロも、アイドルでしかないし、歌姫でしかないのに、Divaっていう曲もありますけど、今もう、アイドルであろうと、なんか、なってるのに、...
Sora-chan, listen to me. Siro is also an idol and a diva, and I even have a song called 'Diva,' but now, even though I'm trying to be an idol,

169
00:16:58,117 --> 00:17:02,617
努力してくれる姿がもう、大好きで、食べたいくらい。
I love how hard you work so much, I want to eat you up.

170
00:17:02,617 --> 00:17:03,617
食べちゃうの？
You're going to eat me?

171
00:17:03,617 --> 00:17:05,617
シナモロールみたいですね。
You look like Cinnamoroll.

172
00:17:05,617 --> 00:17:07,617
見て、カメラさん見て見て！
Look! Cameraman, look, look!

173
00:17:07,617 --> 00:17:09,617
これシナモロール？
Is this Cinnamoroll?

174
00:17:09,617 --> 00:17:11,617
シナモロール。
Cinnamoroll.

175
00:17:10,617 --> 00:17:13,117
食べられちゃう、食べられちゃう。
I'm being eaten, I'm being eaten!

176
00:17:13,117 --> 00:17:14,617
美味しい。
Delicious.

177
00:17:15,617 --> 00:17:18,617
はあ、はい、ということで、
Whew, yes, and so...

178
00:17:18,617 --> 00:17:21,617
今日はBANされない発言を心がけていきます！
Today, I will try my best to avoid saying anything that gets us banned!

179
00:17:21,617 --> 00:17:25,617
もうすでに結構シロちゃんワールド炸裂してますけど。
Siro-chan's world has already exploded quite a bit, though.

180
00:17:26,117 --> 00:17:32,617
あの、なんか、こんな大好きなそらちゃんの、こんな場に、そらともさんたちと、一緒に呼んでもらえると思わなくて。ありがとうございます。
I never thought I'd be invited to such a place for my beloved Sora-chan, alongside the Soratomos. Thank you so much.

181
00:17:32,617 --> 00:17:35,617
3年ぶりだよ！
It's been three years!

182
00:17:36,117 --> 00:17:39,117
3年ぶりの元カノです。元カノじゃない、
I'm the ex-girlfriend from three years ago. No, not ex-girlfriend!

183
00:17:39,617 --> 00:17:46,617
そらともさん、一緒に、一緒に、独り占めしないので、愛でていきましょう。
Soratomos, let's cherish her together. I won't keep her all to myself.

184
00:17:47,117 --> 00:17:51,617
今日はそらともさんに、シロの来た意味を分からせたいと思います。そらちゃん立ってください。
Today, I want to show the Soratomos the meaning of Siro coming here. Sora-chan, please stand up.

185
00:17:51,617 --> 00:17:53,117
はい。
Sure.

186
00:17:53,617 --> 00:17:57,617
さん、に、いち。
3, 2, 1...

187
00:17:57,617 --> 00:18:00,617
バニーガールズ！
Bunny girls!

188
00:18:01,617 --> 00:18:03,617
このスクショでいいの？ねえ。
Is this screenshot okay? Hey.

189
00:18:03,617 --> 00:18:05,617
千手観音。千手観音。
Thousand-Armed Kannon. Thousand-Armed Kannon.

190
00:18:06,117 --> 00:18:10,117
そらちゃん、新衣装のバニー衣装、プレゼントしに来ました。
Sora-chan, I came to present you with your new bunny outfit!

191
00:18:10,117 --> 00:18:11,117
ありがとう！
Thank you!

192
00:18:11,117 --> 00:18:12,117
どうですか？
How is it?

193
00:18:12,117 --> 00:18:14,617
可愛い！バニーガールも可愛い！
It's cute! The bunny girl is also cute!

194
00:18:14,617 --> 00:18:18,117
ウサギさんって、万年発情してるので、ちょっとハアハアしてもらった...
Since rabbits are in heat all year round, I had you pant a bit...

195
00:18:18,617 --> 00:18:20,617
可愛い〜！
So cute!

196
00:18:22,617 --> 00:18:24,617
私の尻尾あるよ。
I have a tail too.

197
00:18:25,617 --> 00:18:28,117
そうだ、そらちゃんと言えば。
That's right, speaking of Sora-chan...

198
00:18:28,617 --> 00:18:29,617
あ、尻尾は。
Oh, the tail is...

199
00:18:30,117 --> 00:18:32,117
ちょっと、お触りしてもいいですか？
Can I touch it a little?

200
00:18:32,617 --> 00:18:33,117
いいよ。
Sure.

201
00:18:33,617 --> 00:18:34,617
つんつん。
*Poke, poke.*

202
00:18:34,617 --> 00:18:35,617
あっ、あっ、大変！
Oh, oh, this is bad!

203
00:18:36,117 --> 00:18:36,617
何？?
What?

204
00:18:37,117 --> 00:18:39,617
シロ、発情が止まらないので、そろそろお家に帰ります。
Siro's heat won't stop, so it's time for me to go home.

205
00:18:39,617 --> 00:18:41,617
帰っちゃうの？
You're going home?!

206
00:18:41,617 --> 00:18:45,617
はい。月からみんなを見守っています。このあとも楽しんで！
Yes. I'll watch over everyone from the moon. Enjoy the rest of the show!

207
00:18:45,617 --> 00:18:47,617
楽しんで！ありがとう！
Have fun! Thank you!

208
00:18:48,117 --> 00:18:50,617
とっとっとっとっと...
*Pitter-patter...*

209
00:18:51,617 --> 00:18:53,617
本当に...あっ、なんか出てきてる。
Really... Oh, something is coming out.

210
00:18:56,617 --> 00:18:58,617
ちょっと！帰れてないよ！...
Hey! You haven't actually gone home!

211
00:19:02,617 --> 00:19:06,617
シロちゃんワールド炸裂で、楽しかったね。
Siro-chan's world exploded, it was so much fun.

212
00:19:06,617 --> 00:19:10,117
なんだこれはって言わないでね、みんな。ねえ。
Everyone, please don't ask 'What on earth was that?' Okay?

213
00:19:10,617 --> 00:19:15,617
でも、相変わらずのシロちゃんで、私、一緒に歌えて、とっても楽しかったです。
But as always, she was Siro-chan. I had so much fun singing with her.

214
00:19:15,617 --> 00:19:21,617
マイペースだね。ねえ、マイペースだよ。私もマイペースだから、良いコンビってことだ！
She goes at her own pace. She really does. I'm also my own pace, so we make a good pair!

215
00:19:21,617 --> 00:19:27,117
というわけで、続いてのゲストに行きましょう。この人です！...
And with that, let's move on to the next guest. Here they are!

216
00:20:13,958 --> 00:20:16,958
全部 全部 アンタのせいだ
It's all, it's all your fault

